stdout | src/app/__tests__/bugfix/test-watch-mode-resource-fix.exploration.test.ts > Test Watch Mode Resource Fix - Bug Condition Exploration > should document expected behavior after fixes are applied

=== EXPECTED BEHAVIOR AFTER FIXES ===

1. Default Resource Limits (Local Development):
   - maxConcurrency: 2 (safe for MacBook Pro)
   - maxWorkers: 2 (safe for MacBook Pro)
   - maxForks: 2 (matches maxWorkers)
   - CPU usage stays under 150% during test execution
   - System remains responsive during tests

2. Test Command Behavior:
   - All non-watch commands include --run flag
   - Tests execute once and exit immediately
   - No indefinite watch mode activation
   - Process releases all CPU and memory resources after completion

3. CI Performance (Preserved):
   - test:full uses --maxConcurrency=4 --maxWorkers=4 overrides
   - CI execution time remains fast (no performance regression)
   - Command-line overrides take precedence over config defaults

4. Watch Mode (Preserved):
   - test:watch continues to run in watch mode
   - test:button:watch continues to work
   - test:ui-components:watch continues to work
   - test:integration:watch continues to work
   - Watch mode commands correctly omit --run flag

=== ROOT CAUSES IDENTIFIED ===

Root Cause 1: Aggressive Default Resource Limits
  - vitest.config.ts sets maxConcurrency: 4, maxWorkers: 4 as defaults
  - These limits are appropriate for CI but too aggressive for local dev
  - MacBook Pro experiences excessive CPU usage (>200%) with 4 workers
  - System becomes sluggish, affecting other applications
  - Fix: Change defaults to maxConcurrency: 2, maxWorkers: 2

Root Cause 2: No Environment-Specific Configuration
  - Current config does not differentiate between local dev and CI
  - Same aggressive limits apply everywhere
  - Local development suffers from resource overload
  - Fix: Use conservative defaults, let CI override via command-line flags

Root Cause 3: Watch Mode as Default Behavior (if applicable)
  - Vitest defaults to watch mode when --run flag is absent
  - Watch mode runs indefinitely, consuming resources continuously
  - Combined with aggressive limits, this severely impacts performance
  - Fix: Ensure all non-watch commands have --run flag

=== FIX STRATEGY ===

1. Modify vitest.config.ts:
   - Change maxConcurrency from 4 to 2
   - Change maxWorkers from 4 to 2
   - Change poolOptions.forks.maxForks from 4 to 2

2. Verify package.json (likely already correct):
   - Confirm all non-watch commands have --run flag
   - Confirm test:full has --maxConcurrency=4 --maxWorkers=4 overrides
   - Confirm watch commands correctly omit --run flag

3. Minimal, Surgical Change:
   - Only change default values in vitest.config.ts
   - No changes to package.json scripts (already correct)
   - CI performance preserved through command-line overrides
   - Local development becomes safe by default

